      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA03d195n1-ptr" id="PJA03d195n1">1</a>
      
   <p>That is, at Harvard College.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA03d195n2-ptr" id="PJA03d195n2">2</a>
      
   <p>The Connecticut enlistments actually ran out on 10 Dec., although even Washington believed they ran out on the 1st (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Allen French, &lt;i&gt;The First Year of the American Revolution, Boston&lt;/i&gt;, 1934. ]">French, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">First Year</span></span>, p. 514; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Writings of George Washington from the Original Manuscript Sources&lt;/i&gt;, 17451799, ed. John C. Fitzpatrick, Washington, 19311944; 39 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Writings</span>, ed. Fitzpatrick</span>, 3:506).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA03d195n3-ptr" id="PJA03d195n3">3</a>
      
   <p>Freely, how can there be freedom when money alone rules?</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA03d195n4-ptr" id="PJA03d195n4">4</a>
      
   <p>See Tudor to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, 28 Oct., <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-03-02-0137&amp;expandNote=PJA03d154n9#PJA03d154n9" class="document">note 9</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA03d195n5-ptr" id="PJA03d195n5">5</a>
      
   <p>The <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Concord;</span> see Joseph Palmer to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, 2 Dec., <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-03-02-0175&amp;expandNote=PJA03d193n13#PJA03d193n13" class="document">note 13</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA03d195n6-ptr" id="PJA03d195n6">6</a>
      
   <p>See <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Legal Papers of John Adams&lt;/i&gt;, ed. L. Kinvin Wroth and Hiller B. Zobel, Cambridge, 1965; 3 vols. ]">JA, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Legal Papers</span></span>, 3:344.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA03d195n7-ptr" id="PJA03d195n7">7</a>
      
   <p>I am delighted to be praised by one who is praised by all men.</p>

